1. NumPy & Pandas
Purpose: Data manipulation and numerical computations.
NumPy (numpy) is used to perform fast mathematical calculations on arrays and matrices.
Pandas (pandas) is used to read, organize, clean, and analyze data in tables (called DataFrames).
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

data = pd.read_csv("students.csv")
2. Matplotlib & Seaborn
Purpose: Data visualization.
These libraries create charts and graphs to help you understand your data.
Matplotlib: Basic plots like line charts, bar charts, pie charts.
Seaborn: More attractive and advanced statistical graphs such as heatmaps and box plots.
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
3. Scikit-learn
Purpose: Machine Learning.
It helps you:
Prepare data
Train machine learning models
Test model accuracy
Make predictions
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
4. XGBoost
Purpose: Advanced machine learning algorithm.
It is used to build highly accurate prediction models and is popular in data science competitions.
from xgboost import XGBClassifier
5. Flask
Purpose: Web application development.
After your machine learning model is ready, Flask helps create a web application where users can enter data and receive predictions.
from flask import Flask
6.Pickle
Purpose: Save and load trained models.
Instead of training your model every time, you can save it to a file and load it later.
import pickle
